% Kirkman's fifteen schoolgirls, framed as a Social Golfer instance: 15
% golfers in 5 groups of 3, scheduled for 7 weeks so no pair of golfers ever
% shares a group more than once. Each golfer shares a group with
% group_size - 1 = 2 others per week, so 7 weeks uses exactly
% 7 * 5 * C(3,2) = 105 = C(15,2) pairs — every pair exactly once, and the
% most weeks any 5-3 schedule can reach. Since n_groups (5) is not a
% multiple of group_size (3), model.mzn's week-2 transversal symmetry break
% does not apply to this instance (its `if` guard is false); only the
% weaker per-week ordering symmetry breaks are active.

n_groups   = 5;
group_size = 3;
n_weeks    = 7;
